<TITLE> Hafizuddin looks to court for an end to infighting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com)  Pro-reformist BNP leader Hafizuddin Ahmed Wednesday said the court would decide who would be the secretary general of the embattled BNP. "We want a united BNP. The contention over the post of secretary general will be settled in court. We are waiting for it," Hafizuddin, disputed acting secretary general of the party, told reporters after a meeting with party colleagues at his Banani home. Former secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan and other leaders retired lieutenant general Mahbubur Rahman, former MP Abdul Alim, Shah Md Abul Hossain, ZA Khan and AHM Mofazzal Karim were present at the meeting. "We want to strengthen the party through reforms. The party will be united under the leadership of (BNP chairperson) Khaleda Zia and will take part in the next election," he said. The BNP leader claimed that there was no conflict in BNP. He said they wanted to unite BNP, removing all conflicts over reforms. "Our acting chairman M Saifur Rahman called for unity in the party," he said. It was the first meeting of Hafizuddin with senior leaders after he was made acting secretary general at the standing committee meeting on Oct 29. bdnews24.
